The Chronicle Tonderai Zvimba, Showbiz Reporter
DSTV’s Zambezi Magic is looking for presenters who can host the reality show Our Perfect Wedding Zimbabwe. Last year Zambezi Magic announced that they were looking for local content producers to produce the Zimbabwean version of the South African reality show Our Perfect Wedding. Zambezi Magic TV (Channel 160) announced on their Facebook page that they are looking for a presenter to host the upcoming reality show. “Blessed with the gift of the garb and the ability to keep viewers spellbound as the host of a perfect wedding event? Are you a confident talker, do you think you have what it takes to keep viewers enthralled by your flawless delivery and ability to warm your way into everyone’s heart? Then we are looking for you.” <img class=" wp-image-435261" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2019/02/Bathabile-360x252.jpg" alt="" width="689" height="482" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2019/02/Bathabile-360x252.jpg 360w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2019/02/Bathabile.jpg 680w" sizes="(max-width: 689px) 100vw, 689px" /> Bathabile Dlamini In the comments section of the post, people tagged personalities who they thought could make the cut. <img class=" wp-image-427124" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2018/11/Nyasha-Mtamangira-360x209.jpg" alt="" width="704" height="409" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2018/11/Nyasha-Mtamangira-360x209.jpg 360w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2018/11/Nyasha-Mtamangira.jpg 680w" sizes="(max-width: 704px) 100vw, 704px" /> Nyasha Diva Mtamangira Names such as TLC presenter search finalist Karen Mukwedeya, Nyasha Diva Mtamangira and Bathabile Dlamini were being thrown into the fray. <img class=" wp-image-280764" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2016/10/Karen_Paida_Mukwedeya_.original-300x246.jpg" alt="" width="595" height="488" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2016/10/Karen_Paida_Mukwedeya_.original-300x246.jpg 300w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2016/10/Karen_Paida_Mukwedeya_.original.jpg 640w" sizes="(max-width: 595px) 100vw, 595px" /> Karen Paida Mukwedeya Those who follow the South African series have fallen in love with the likes of Kayise Nqula, Nomsa Buthelezi, Tumi Morake, Anele Mdoda and Jessica Nkosi. OPW Zimbabwe will be the second spin-off version to the original South African series which airs on Dstv’s Mzansi Magic on Sundays at 7PM. Zambezi Magic already has Our Perfect Wedding Zambia. Those interested in hosting the show are required to apply on the Zambezi Magic TV website and are also required to upload a one minute video of them presenting an episode of OPW Zim. The closing date for submissions is March 31 and those who would have made it will be notified.